itivity follow-up: SSE and WebSocket parity must prove that streaming and replay handoff preserve the same disclosure-control behavior as CLI and REST, including no-leak guarantees for safe previews and redaction markers.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:24Z"},{"id":377,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","author":"codex","text":"Priority raised to P1 after plan-space audit: streaming parity is a user-facing contract and a disclosure boundary, not secondary plumbing. Once 4.8 and 8.1 are done, SSE and WebSocket should converge before validation or docs treat the redesign as finished.","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:09:25Z"}]}
