ed_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:35.744902360Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":341,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: benchmark and regression coverage should measure idle-heartbeat overhead, filter selectivity costs, cadence adaptation under churn and degraded sources, and the operational cost difference between durable event publication and ephemeral keepalive traffic.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:06Z"},{"id":345,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-performance follow-up: benchmarks must measure replay and as-of latency, cache-hit versus reconstruction cost, payload-size behavior for historical responses, and SQLite churn introduced by replay caching so the feature stays operationally cheap enough for live debugging.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:15Z"},{"id":361,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: benchmark coverage must measure redaction and safe-preview cost on hot surfaces and replay paths so the safety layer remains cheap enough for routine robot consumption.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:28Z"},{"id":370,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: benchmark coverage now explicitly waits for 8.2 so user-facing cost checks include dashboard and alternate-renderer projection work, not only CLI renderers. Measure payload, allocation, and redaction or safe-preview overhead where those projections surface compact evidence.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:40Z"}]}
